title: Three-star safety decommits from Sooners
content: Jarrian Jones  had been on the verge of staying in his home state and committing to Mississippi State before.    But Saturday, the three-star safety pulled the trigger, flipping to the Bulldogs after committing to Oklahoma in April.    In a tweet announcing his decision, Jones said the opportunity to stay close to home was too much to pass up.     Earlier in the day, Oklahoma's 2019 recruiting class had grown to 12 with the commitment from Washington, D.C. product Joseph Wete , a four-star defensive end.    With Jones' decommitment, the Sooners now have 11 commitments in the class, including one defensive back — safety  Jamal Morris .
